Virtual Attributes
- useful for working with legacy databases
- allows you to work with fields that don't directly map to columns in database

Examples
- first name, last name  ==> full_name
- birthdate ==> month, day, year
- if you have a form and want identical info, like to confirm password or email. Adds _confirmation [2.3 confirmation](http://guides.rubyonrails.org/active_record_validations.html)
- to check a box confirming that you read something or agree to it

basically, in model
- define accessor methods: getter and setter methods

- attr_accessor
- attr_accessible
